Welcome to OpenSSL!

   OpenSSL is a robust, commercial-grade, and full-featured toolkit for
   the Transport Layer Security (TLS) and Secure Sockets Layer (SSL)
   protocols. It is also a general-purpose cryptography library. For more
   information about the team and community around the project, or to
   start making your own contributions, start with the community page. To
   get the latest news, download the source, and so on, please see the
   sidebar or the buttons at the top of every page.

   OpenSSL is licensed under an Apache-style license, which basically
   means that you are free to get and use it for commercial and
   non-commercial purposes subject to some simple license conditions.

   For a list of vulnerabilities, and the releases in which they were
   found and fixes, see our Vulnerabilities page.

